FBIS4-8163 "dreeu070_p_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-070 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 POLAND Walesa Receives Bulgarian Foreign Minister Walesa Receives Bulgarian Foreign Minister LD1104163794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1014 GMT 11 Apr 94 LD1104163794 Warsaw PAP Polish BFN [Text] Warsaw, 11 Apr--President Lech Walesa received at the Belweder today Bulgarian Foreign Minister Stanislav Daskalov, who is paying an official two-day visit to Poland. "For many years, we were in the same political and economic orbit, and certain bonds and cooperation were established. Now, when we are reforming our countries, I think we should return to some issues," the president said. According to the president, Poland and Bulgaria should cooperate more actively in the creation of a vision of a new Europe. Daskalov said that Poland and Bulgaria have common goals: integration into the European Community. Daskalov repeated the invitation by President Zhelyu Zhelev for Lech Walesa to visit Bulgaria.
